Continuing from there, Let's make the user type in their age insead of defining it in the code itself.
A1. Replace the line where we define the age variable with the input function use "How old are your?" with the input function and save the recived input in a variable called age_input.
A2. Create a vreable called age and use the int funtion to transform the input into a number like age= int(age_input).
A3. Remove the print function display "How old are you?" to not ask twice.

name = input ("Hello! What is your name?")
print(f"Nice to meet your, {name}!")
age_input = input("How old are you?")
age = int (age_input)
bot_age = 3 
age_difference = age- bot_age
print("you are {age_difference} years older than me. I'm onle {bot_age} years old !")
print("What's Your favorite color?")
color = "blue"
Print(f"Oh, {color} is a beautiful color!")

Finally, let the user share their favorite color insead of pre-fillinit
